  "_readme": "58 real, verified BEP-20 token addresses on BNB Chain (chainId 56), pulled directly from PancakeSwap's own official token-list repository (github.com/pancakeswap/token-list) - src/tokens/pancakeswap-default.json (their strictest, most-vetted list) plus a hand-picked subset of well-known major/blue-chip symbols from src/tokens/pancakeswap-extended.json. None of these addresses were guessed or pulled from memory. This is a reasonable proxy for 'high-liquidity' tokens (established, actively-traded assets), NOT a live TVL-ranked list - PancakeSwap's own token lists don't encode real-time liquidity data. Before relying on any specific pair for real trades, verify it actually has deep liquidity on the DEX you're routing through (check the pool directly, e.g. via the DEX's own UI or getReserves()) - being a real, listed token does not guarantee a deep pool exists for every pair with every other token here. 58 tokens already yields 58*57=3,306 ordered pair combinations, well above the 200-pair requirement, via the same token-graph x router-registry approach in routes.ts.",
